    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1918-12-20">December 20, 1918.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear <persName key="vachel_lindsay">Vachel Lindsay</persName>:-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Of course I like <persName>Franz Rickaby</persName>. Who could help it? I am
                    exceedingly grateful to you for introducing us, but apart entirely from my
                    personal liking for him you must understand that any friends of yours will
                    always be a friend of mine.</p>
                <p>There are a great many things that I want to talk over with you some-time. I
                    cannot help feeling in spite of your generosity that you are a bit hurt at my
                    not including you in <title key="tendencies">“Tendencies.”</title> It was not because of lack of merit, it was
                    simply that your work did not fit into the scheme of my book, and I never
                    intended that book to <add place="above" type="insertion" rend="typed">be</add> a complete treatment of modern poetry, merely a
                    presentation of a few obvious sections. Some time I hope to have a chance of
                    writing on your work alone, and then you will know my real opinion. In the
                    meanwhile, at least you know that I am always and most sincerely</p>
                <closer>Your friend,</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
